  <chapter number="2" style="c" sid="2CO 2" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="2CO 2:1" />Getting to the point, I made up my mind that I wouldn’t visit you again while laden with the pains of
        sorrow. <verse eid="2CO 2:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="2CO 2:2" />In fact, if I’m making you feel sorry, who in particular will cheer me up apart from the one I made feel
        sorry? <verse eid="2CO 2:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="2CO 2:3" />The very thing I wrote, I wrote so that I wouldn’t come for a visit and wind up being made sorry<char
        style="sup">[a]</char> by the ones I ought to rejoice over, as my nearness to you all has convinced me
        that my joy is derived from you all. <verse eid="2CO 2:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="2CO 2:4" />In fact, what I wrote to you through many tears came out of a great deal of distress and heart-felt anguish,
        not so that it would cause you sorrow, but so that you’d understand the abundant love which I have for
        you.<verse eid="2CO 2:4" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="2CO 2:5" />If a certain person has caused sorrow, he hasn’t caused me sorrow (<char style="it">actually </char>no,
        <char style="it">he has </char>partially), so I won’t dump<char style="sup">[b]</char> <char style="it">any
        more of this</char> on you all. <verse eid="2CO 2:5" />
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="2CO 2:6" />The very punishment <char style="it">inflicted </char>by the many is enough for such a person, <verse eid="2CO 2:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="2CO 2:7" />so that on the flip-side, you <char style="it">should be</char> all the more kind and merciful <char
        style="it">to him </char>and comfort and encourage <char style="it">him</char>, <char style="it">so that</char>
        such a person not somehow be deluged with even more sorrow. <verse eid="2CO 2:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="2CO 2:8" />In light of this I advise you to broadcast<char style="sup">[c]</char> love to him. <verse eid="2CO 2:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="2CO 2:9" />In fact, another reason I wrote is so that I could discern if you live up to my standards, <char style="it">that
        is </char>if you obey everything you’re told. <verse eid="2CO 2:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="2CO 2:10" />Now if you forgive <char style="it">somebody of </char>something, so do I; you see, if in addition <char
        style="it">to you </char>I <char style="it">forgave somebody of something</char>, what I’ve forgiven
        (assuming there’s something I’m forgiving), <char style="it">I did so </char>through you under the scrutiny<char
        style="sup">[d]</char> of Christ, <verse eid="2CO 2:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="2CO 2:11" />so that we won’t be swindled by Satan: we are not ignorant of his intentions, you see.<verse eid="2CO 2:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="2CO 2:12" />Now that I’ve arrived at Troas for the purpose of spreading the Gospel of Christ (i.e., the good news
        about Christ), a door has been opened to me in the Lord (i.e., in regard to the things of the Lord, a
        tremendous opportunity has presented itself to me), <verse eid="2CO 2:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="2CO 2:13" />I was uncomfortable<char style="sup">[e]</char> in my spirit not finding my fellow-comrade<char style="sup">[f]</char>
        Titus, so instead I excused myself, said goodbye to them, and left for Macedonia.<verse eid="2CO 2:13" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="2CO 2:14" />But thank-you God, Who always makes us roadies on Christ’s victory tour<char style="sup">[A]</char>,
        and Who’s propagating the fragrance of his knowledge<char style="sup">[g]</char> through us in all regions,<verse eid="2CO 2:14" />
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="2CO 2:15" />since in God we are a pleasant<char style="sup">[h]</char> aroma (<char style="it">like the incense they
        burned in the Old Testament, or the pleasing smell of a burnt offering</char>) of Christ among those
        being saved (i.e., those being rescued from calamity) and among those perishing; <verse eid="2CO 2:15" />
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="2CO 2:16" />we who on the one hand <char style="it">are </char>a whiff <char style="it">of going </char>from death
        to <char style="it">even more </char>death<char style="sup">[B]</char>, and on the other hand <char style="it">are
        </char>a whiff <char style="it">of going </char>from life to <char style="it">even more </char>life—and
        that’s not good enough for some people? <verse eid="2CO 2:16" />
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="2CO 2:17" />You see, we’re not like so many <char style="it">other preachers </char>who hustle<char style="sup">[i]</char>
        the word of God—no—<char style="it">we preach the Gospel </char>like it’s coming from someone who’s sincere
        through-and-through<char style="sup">[j]</char>—no—we speak <char style="it">the word of God </char>in
        Christ like it’s coming directly from God <char style="it">while</char> <char style="it">we</char> <char
        style="it">stand</char> before God<char style="sup">[k]</char>.<verse eid="2CO 2:17" />
    </para>
