        <char style="it">with</char> [or <char style="it">to</char>] <char style="it">God at the indescribable
        gift of His</char></char>
      <char style="fp"></char>
    </note>
    <note caller="[A]" style="f">
      <char style="fk">[A]</char>
      <char style="ft"><char style="it">bread for the food that you eat</char>…Lit: <char style="it">bread for food</char>.
        the majority of one’s calories were derived from eating bread in ancient times. In the context of the
        writing of this epistle, therefore, bread was what people survived on (ref. Matt. 6:11). So saying that
        God will supply bread for food means that God will supply what you need to eat.</char>
    </note>
  <chapter eid="2CO 9" />
